 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Sudden Light</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="cinquain">
     <l n="1" met="+--+-+|+-+--+|-+-+-+|-++--+|--++-+">I have been here before,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+-+-+-+">But when or how I cannot tell:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+-+-+-+">I know the grass beyond the door,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+++">The sweet keen smell,</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+-+-+-+-+">The sighing sound, the lights around the shore.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="cinquain">
     <l n="6" met="+--+-+">You have been mine before,--</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+-+-+-+">How long ago I may not know:</l>
     <l n="8" met="-++--+-+">But just when at that swallow's soar</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+++">Your neck turned so,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+-+-+-+-+|++-+-+-+-+">Some veil did fall,--I knew it all of yore.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="cinquain">
     <l n="11" met="++-+-+">Then, now,--perchance again!</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+-+-+-+|++-+-+-+">O round mine eyes your tresses shake!</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+-+-+-+|+--+-+-+|--++--++|+-++--++">Shall we not lie as we have lain</l>
     <l n="14" met="+-++">Thus for Love's sake,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+-+-+-+-+">And sleep, and wake, yet never break the chain?</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
